<p>I have <code>Posts</code> and <code>Comments</code> tables, <code>Comments</code> are related to <code>Posts</code> by <code>postId</code>, and I need to change <code>DateUpdated</code> field in <code>Posts</code> table when inserting new <code>Comment</code> entity.</p>  <p>Is there any way to do this with one query and how to do it properly if it is not?</p>  <p>Now I`m doing this way:</p>  <pre><code>context.Comments.Add(comment); context.SaveChanges();  context.Posts .Single(p =&gt; p.Comments.Contains(c =&gt; comment.Id) .DateUpdated = DateTime.Now; context.SaveChanges(); </code></pre>